I don’t talk about this very often- but I am sober and have just celebrated my 11th sober anniversary 💗 I think it’s important to share this information because I am so proud of myself and sobriety has been like a rebirth for me. It’s allowed me to dream and to show up for myself and for others in a way that I wasn’t able before. 
Being in the depths & darkness of substance use filled a lot of voids for me in a way that allowed me not to confront the issues in my life. I was living in a lot of fear and mostly unable to confront it. For me I had to make a decision to stop placating those issues and start facing my demons one day at a time. 
Everybody has their own path and journey, but today I feel the most immense gratitude towards my sober angels that have guided me and held my hand through some very difficult years. Thank you for reminding me always that I am not alone ❤️
